description:
This is one of the best restaurant in SF.  The atmosphere is quaint--as if you stepped into someone's living room.  The service has always been fast, efficient, and friendly.  Most importantly, every dish bursts with surprising flavors!  The menu is priced just right so you get incredible value as well!  Your experience here will exceed any experience at Burma Super Star (which I believe has an overpriced menu.  The food is good at Burma Super Star, but not nearly as good as Mandalay...however, Burma Super Star has one of my favorite drinks: the Burmese Ginger Beer).

Mandalay's LUNCH SPECIALS are also an unbeatable value.  Their $8 to $10 lunch specials run from Mondays thru Fridays and includes a salad, main dish, soup, bowl of rice...and of course a pot of tea.  The portions are plentiful.  Pair up your lunch special with a BURMESE ICE TEA for $1.75 more.

My favorite dishes here include:  
(1) TEA LEAF SALAD (the myriad textures and bursts of flavors--from the bitter-sweet lemon juices, to the crunch of the fried onion rings, to the soft and succulent tea leaves--are unbelievable;
(2) Rangoon Beef;
(3) Stir fried string beans;
(4)  Balada--an appetizer bread dish with curry sauce;
(5) Papaya salad

I've tried their lamb curry...it's tender and succulent, but I think New Eritrea has better curry dishes (but that's just being scrupulous).

Only concern:  parking may be a bit of a hassle....so plan accordingly.
